Amendment No. 2 to SB1255
Lamar
Signature of Sponsor
AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 1255* House Bill No. 1369
by deleting all language after the enacting clause and substituting:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 68, Chapter 1, Part 1, is amended by
adding the following as a new section:
The department of health shall make available and require educational materials
on blood lead level testing for a pregnant woman who receives vouchers for the special
supplemental food program for women, infants, and children. The department of health
shall also provide the woman educational information on specialized nutritional services,
education on how to mitigate lead in the body, and other existing wraparound services
tailored for people with elevated blood lead levels or lead poisoning.
SECTION 2. This act takes effect upon becoming a law, the public welfare requiring it.
